WEBVTT

00:04.037 --> 00:07.040
Henri insisted
I show it to you first

00:07.040 --> 00:09.076
before it's in any stores.

00:09.076 --> 00:12.012
Whoo-hoo.
(Laughs) Naughty.

00:12.012 --> 00:13.113
(Chuckles)

00:13.113 --> 00:14.114
Pass.

00:14.114 --> 00:16.015
Oh.

00:16.015 --> 00:17.084
Go.

00:17.084 --> 00:21.021
From salon de gorgeous...

00:21.021 --> 00:22.089
(Letitia) Oh.

00:22.089 --> 00:24.992
Oh.

00:24.992 --> 00:28.028
Oh. Thrilling.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.997
Pass.

00:29.997 --> 00:32.098
Are you gonna say no
to everything I like?

00:32.098 --> 00:34.034
Ding, ding, ding.

00:34.034 --> 00:38.038
No one wants to buy lingerie
their mother approves of.

00:38.038 --> 00:42.075
I'm sorry, Adrian.
I'm just--I'm not feeling it.

00:44.011 --> 00:46.013
What's the matter with you?

00:46.013 --> 00:48.015
Nothing. I guess...

00:48.015 --> 00:50.083
I guess when I--
when I buy underwear,

00:50.083 --> 00:52.085
I just need to have
someone in mind.

00:52.085 --> 00:55.022
And well, mom,
let's face it,

00:55.022 --> 00:57.124
after four failed marriages--
four--and oh, oh,

00:57.124 --> 01:00.027
and a failed wedding
where I was traded for stock--

01:00.027 --> 01:02.095
nonsense. You're--you're
momentarily unhappy.

01:02.095 --> 01:04.096
And why wouldn't you be?

01:04.096 --> 01:07.067
Oh, I can't tell you
the number of times

01:07.067 --> 01:09.036
I've been disappointed by men.

01:09.036 --> 01:11.038
Mm.

01:11.038 --> 01:14.007
But do you know
what never lets me down,

01:14.007 --> 01:15.075
not ever?

01:15.075 --> 01:18.011
Oh, oh, oh, well,
if it has batteries, mom,

01:18.011 --> 01:20.013
I'd really rather not.

01:20.013 --> 01:23.016
Oh, no. I'm talking
about you, dear.

01:23.016 --> 01:25.052
Aw. (Chuckles)

01:25.052 --> 01:28.021
You and my other
wonderful children--

01:28.021 --> 01:30.123
you are the great joys
of my life.

01:30.123 --> 01:32.993
Oh.

01:32.993 --> 01:35.996
Someday you'll know
what I mean.

01:35.996 --> 01:37.064
(Man) Children!

01:37.064 --> 01:38.999
(School bell rings)

01:38.999 --> 01:41.001
Children, line up.
Come on, everybody.

01:41.001 --> 01:44.004
Let's go. Let's go.
Shake a leg. Shake a leg.

01:44.004 --> 01:45.072
(Car horn honks)

01:45.072 --> 01:47.007
(Nick) Hey! Hey.

01:47.007 --> 01:49.076
Mr. George.
Here it is.
Here it is. I made it.

01:49.076 --> 01:52.045
Uh, Mr. George?
Yeah, I forgot
Kiki's permission slip

01:52.045 --> 01:54.114
when I dropped her off
yesterday, for the field trip.

01:54.114 --> 01:56.049
Your wife called and said

01:56.049 --> 01:59.052
Kiki wouldn't be coming
to school today.
What?

01:59.052 --> 02:01.054
Hi, Mr. George.
Hey, Molly.

02:01.054 --> 02:04.091
Where's Kiki?
Uh, I'm trying to
figure that out right now.

02:04.091 --> 02:07.027
Uh, when--when did my wife call
and say this?
This morning.

02:07.027 --> 02:09.062
She said they were gone
for the weekend.

02:09.062 --> 02:11.064
Is there a problem?

02:11.064 --> 02:12.099
(Sighs)

02:12.099 --> 02:15.002
(Keypad beeps,
cell phone rings)

02:15.002 --> 02:17.037
The problem?

02:17.037 --> 02:20.107
The problem is that you didn't
tell me you were taking her.
It was a last-minute thing,
Nick.

02:20.107 --> 02:23.043
This client called
out of the blue.

02:23.043 --> 02:25.078
It's a beautiful house
right on the beach.

02:25.078 --> 02:28.081
I'm going to select
some art pieces--
look, I don't care if you're
painting them yourself

02:28.081 --> 02:31.084
with finger paints, Lisa,
you can't kidnap our daughter.
I am not having
this conversation.

02:31.084 --> 02:34.087
You are obviously insane. I will
have her back to you on Monday.
On Monday?
This is my weekend, Lisa.

02:34.087 --> 02:36.123
We made an agreement.
(Cell phone beeps)

02:36.123 --> 02:38.992
Lisa? Lisa?!

02:38.992 --> 02:40.093
(Beep)

02:40.093 --> 02:42.095
It feels pretty homey.

02:42.095 --> 02:44.097
I mean, I've only
been here a day,

02:44.097 --> 02:47.067
but I'm already getting
the sense that, um,

02:47.067 --> 02:49.069
this is where I belong.

02:49.069 --> 02:51.071
(Tripp)
That's so wonderful, son.

02:51.071 --> 02:53.106
So what can I do
for you, dad?

02:53.106 --> 02:56.076
A few years ago,

02:56.076 --> 02:59.112
we put the kibosh on
Simon elder's bio-fuel project.

02:59.112 --> 03:02.015
And now he's your partner,

03:02.015 --> 03:04.051
so his profits
are your profits.

03:04.051 --> 03:06.019
Precisely.

03:06.019 --> 03:08.021
The key to the whole business

03:08.021 --> 03:10.023
was the chairman
of the committee--

03:10.023 --> 03:11.124
a fellow named Charles Watley.

03:11.124 --> 03:13.126
Now if he could be persuaded...
(Elevator bell dings)

03:13.126 --> 03:16.096
To reverse his position,
that would be very beneficial

03:16.096 --> 03:19.032
to everybody.
I'll talk to him, dad,
but that's it.

03:19.032 --> 03:20.100
I'm not gonna push.

03:20.100 --> 03:22.069
No, no, no, no.

03:22.069 --> 03:24.071
Just feel him out,
see where he stands, you know?

03:24.071 --> 03:27.040
Yes, but I'm not
going to be unethical.

03:27.040 --> 03:29.042
I'll see what I can do.

03:29.042 --> 03:31.044
Thanks. Bye.

03:31.044 --> 03:32.112
You okay?

03:32.112 --> 03:35.115
Yeah. Uh... look,
I need to borrow a jet.

03:35.115 --> 03:38.085
Lisa took Kiki out of state
for the weekend

03:38.085 --> 03:40.988
without my permission,
without even notifying me.
Oh, wow.

03:40.988 --> 03:44.024
Yeah. So I had the GPS company
track the location of the car,

03:44.024 --> 03:47.060
and they're somewhere near
the Maryland shore.
You want to go there
and retrieve Kiki.

03:47.060 --> 03:50.030
Yeah.
Take the plane. Go.

03:50.030 --> 03:52.065
(Nick)
All right. Thanks.

03:52.065 --> 03:54.067
(Jeremy) Oh, yeah.
(Exhales deeply)

03:54.067 --> 03:57.104
That's what it takes. Whoo!
The memories are flooding back.

03:57.104 --> 04:00.107
How long do you think
you can keep this up?
All morning.

04:00.107 --> 04:03.043
Mm. I mean the amnesia act.

04:03.043 --> 04:05.112
Mm. As long as it takes
to convince Simon

04:05.112 --> 04:07.114
that I remember
absolutely nothing

04:07.114 --> 04:09.049
about how he's got

04:09.049 --> 04:11.051
your little brother
tucked away somewhere.

04:11.051 --> 04:13.053
Then I'll move in,
gain Simon's trust,

04:13.053 --> 04:16.055
get close enough to figure out
where he stashed the kid.

04:16.055 --> 04:19.059
Baby... you're not really
spy material,

04:19.059 --> 04:23.063
not to mention that Simon is
a paranoid sociopath...

04:23.063 --> 04:26.033
And that's on a good day.

04:26.033 --> 04:30.003
You're never
gonna get close to him.

04:30.003 --> 04:33.073
Unless he thinks
it's his idea.

04:33.073 --> 04:36.009
Mm.

04:36.009 --> 04:39.079
So let's make him think
it's his idea.

04:43.050 --> 04:46.019
(Nick) Here's a crazy idea...
(Clark) Hello, Mr. George.

04:46.019 --> 04:47.988
Since it's just you and me
on this trip, Clark,

04:47.988 --> 04:49.990
how about you switch
the satellite radio

04:49.990 --> 04:51.992
to something
a little less operatic?

04:51.992 --> 04:55.095
Oh, it's not just
you and me, Mr. George.
What are you talking about?

04:55.095 --> 04:58.098
I'm stowing away. What do you
want to do, listen to N. P. R.?

04:58.098 --> 05:01.101
It's not gonna happen.
Yeah? Well, I'm taking
the jet to D. C., Brian.

05:01.101 --> 05:04.071
Oh, yeah? So am I.
Yeah, for what?

05:04.071 --> 05:06.106
It's classified.
I could tell you, but...

05:06.106 --> 05:10.043
That might lead to
an actual conversation.
God forbid.

05:10.043 --> 05:12.112
Hey, Clark. Let's blow
this popsicle stand.

05:12.112 --> 05:15.015
Uh, as soon as the last
passenger boards the aircraft,

05:15.015 --> 05:17.017
Mr. Darling,
the stand will be blown.

05:17.017 --> 05:19.019
What last passenger?

05:19.019 --> 05:21.088
Hello, sailors.
Going my way? Sorry.

05:21.088 --> 05:24.024
That depends.
Where you going?
And the answer is no.

05:24.024 --> 05:26.026
Uh, little place
outside of D. C.

05:26.026 --> 05:28.128
It's, um, a boutique of sorts,
very exclusive.

05:28.128 --> 05:31.031
Yeah? What are you
shopping for, jewelry?

05:31.031 --> 05:32.065
Nope. Mnh-mnh.

05:32.065 --> 05:35.068
So... what are you
going for?

05:35.068 --> 05:36.103
Sperm.

05:38.071 --> 05:40.007
Sperm?

05:40.007 --> 05:41.074
Yeah, you heard me.

05:41.074 --> 05:43.010
Buckle up, boys.

05:43.010 --> 05:44.077
Karen Darling...

05:44.077 --> 05:47.047
(Singsong voice)
Is gonna have a baby.

05:47.047 --> 05:50.017
♪♪♪

06:00.060 --> 06:02.095
Mommy kind of gave me
the idea,

06:02.095 --> 06:05.098
and at first,
I was totally against it.

06:05.098 --> 06:09.002
I mean, baby poo
and holding... things?

06:09.002 --> 06:10.103
But once I got a physical

06:10.103 --> 06:13.106
and started doing research
on sperm and their banks,

06:13.106 --> 06:15.075
what can I say?

06:15.075 --> 06:18.011
You got sucked in?
I did.

06:18.011 --> 06:20.013
What a lovely thought,
Karen.

06:20.013 --> 06:22.082
Don't. Do not--do not try
and talk me out of this.

06:22.082 --> 06:24.117
You stopped me
from marrying Simon.

06:24.117 --> 06:28.021
Don't stop me from having coco.
(Nick and Brian) Coco?

06:28.021 --> 06:30.090
That's gonna be its name.

06:30.090 --> 06:32.092
I'm gonna pick out a donor

06:32.092 --> 06:35.996
and I'm gonna schedule a squirt
or whatever it is they call it.

06:35.996 --> 06:37.097
Support me, people. Come on.

06:37.097 --> 06:39.099
Well, I want to, Karen. I do.

06:39.099 --> 06:42.069
I just think that...
You with a kid?

06:42.069 --> 06:45.105
Oh, yeah, like you have anything
to teach anyone about parenting?

06:45.105 --> 06:48.075
Don't start with me, Brian.
The minute you and Lisa
broke up,

06:48.075 --> 06:50.077
you should've gone
to the authorities

06:50.077 --> 06:53.080
and accused her of child abuse
and loose living.
It's true.

06:53.080 --> 06:55.115
Well, that wouldn't
have been true.
You know, so what?

06:55.115 --> 06:58.085
At least you wouldn't be
on this mission,

06:58.085 --> 07:01.021
going to kidnap
your own kid back.

07:01.021 --> 07:03.090
When it comes to kids, Nick,
you gotta play dirty.

07:03.090 --> 07:05.092
Well, thanks for
the advice, padre.

07:05.092 --> 07:08.095
Hey, what are you going
to D. C. For anyway?

07:10.030 --> 07:14.034
Well... you know,
if you two need to know...

07:14.034 --> 07:17.104
I'm giving a benediction

07:17.104 --> 07:20.107
for a state dinner
that Patrick's hosting.
(Thud, metal clattering)

07:20.107 --> 07:23.010
Sorry about that, folks.

07:23.010 --> 07:25.078
We're heading into
a little bit of chop.

07:25.078 --> 07:27.047
It should even out in no time.

07:27.047 --> 07:29.049
Wait, Tripp isn't going
to paddy's dinner?

07:29.049 --> 07:32.019
That seems kind of odd
for him.
Well, I guess paddy

07:32.019 --> 07:34.021
wants everyone to
stay the hell out of it

07:34.021 --> 07:36.123
and maybe mind
their own business maybe.
(Metal rattles)

07:36.123 --> 07:39.092
Okay. Okay, okay.
That can't be good, can it?

07:39.092 --> 07:41.995
Hey, Brian,
my guess is that God feels

07:41.995 --> 07:44.064
the same way about you
that everyone else does.

07:44.064 --> 07:47.067
But just in case he's, like,
a big-picture kinda guy,

07:47.067 --> 07:50.037
maybe you could just
toss out a prayer.

07:50.037 --> 07:52.072
No, I am not gonna pray
to God for protection

07:52.072 --> 07:54.074
from a world
that he made dangerous.

07:54.074 --> 07:56.043
Just tough it out.

07:56.043 --> 07:58.011
(Clattering)

07:58.011 --> 08:00.013
Okay, I'm gonna put
a word in, all right?

08:00.013 --> 08:03.016
So just bow
your friggin' heads.

08:03.016 --> 08:05.018
Anxious? (Laughs)
No, not at all.

08:05.018 --> 08:07.020
Because there's no reason to be.

08:07.020 --> 08:10.023
Everything's going as planned.

08:10.023 --> 08:12.092
It's not overconfidence.
It's just--

08:12.092 --> 08:15.028
hey, hey, hey.
Do not threaten me.

08:15.028 --> 08:18.031
When I have I ever given you
reason to doubt my loyalty?

08:18.031 --> 08:20.067
When have I ever--

08:22.002 --> 08:24.004
okay. All right.
Okay. All right.

08:24.004 --> 08:26.006
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

08:26.006 --> 08:28.008
Uh...

08:28.008 --> 08:31.011
I promise, I'll get it done.

08:31.011 --> 08:33.113
Listen, nola just arrived.
I gotta go.

08:33.113 --> 08:35.048
(Cell phone beeps)

08:40.020 --> 08:43.023
Sorry I'm late.
What's this?

08:43.023 --> 08:45.125
The minutes to
Patrick Darling's first session

08:45.125 --> 08:48.095
with the senate
agricultural committee.
How'd he do?

08:48.095 --> 08:51.131
He held his own. You'll see.
It's all in there.

08:51.131 --> 08:54.067
Whoa. Wait.
What is that?

08:54.067 --> 08:55.068
What?

08:55.068 --> 08:57.070
You have a hickey.

09:04.111 --> 09:06.079
I do.

09:06.079 --> 09:08.081
And welcome
to eighth grade.

09:08.081 --> 09:11.084
(Chuckles) Who gave it to you?
Who are you seeing?

09:13.053 --> 09:14.988
Jeremy Darling.

09:14.988 --> 09:18.025
Jeremy? Jeremy Darling
has amnesia.

09:18.025 --> 09:20.027
I thought he didn't
remember you.

09:20.027 --> 09:22.062
He didn't. He doesn't.

09:22.062 --> 09:24.064
It just so happens you two

09:24.064 --> 09:27.034
have fallen
into bed together... again?

09:27.034 --> 09:30.037
I guess
we just have chemistry.

09:30.037 --> 09:32.072
Yeah.

09:32.072 --> 09:34.074
Let's hope that's true.

09:34.074 --> 09:36.076
Because if I were
to ever find out

09:36.076 --> 09:39.079
that his amnesia was anything
less than genuine--

09:39.079 --> 09:41.114
he doesn't remember anything.

09:41.114 --> 09:43.083
Trust me.

09:55.028 --> 09:58.999
So... what can I
do for you, senator?

09:58.999 --> 10:01.101
Well, I came to speak to you

10:01.101 --> 10:03.103
about Simon elder's
bio-diesel project.

10:03.103 --> 10:07.007
Which is now a joint venture
with Darling enterprises,

10:07.007 --> 10:09.109
if I'm not mistaken.
That's correct, yes.

10:09.109 --> 10:13.013
And your father would like me
to reverse my negative position

10:13.013 --> 10:16.083
now that there's money to be
made in it for him.
That's... I'm not sure
that's how he would put it.

10:16.083 --> 10:19.019
(Chuckles) Well, of course not,
but then again,

10:19.019 --> 10:21.989
your father never says exactly
what he means, does he?

10:21.989 --> 10:24.091
Look, I'll tell you what--
why don't you tell your father,

10:24.091 --> 10:26.093
please, for me, senator,

10:26.093 --> 10:29.062
that the position that he...
Pressured me into taking

10:29.062 --> 10:30.998
all those many years ago

10:30.998 --> 10:33.033
is one I've actually
come to agree with?

10:33.033 --> 10:37.037
I will not
reverse my position.

10:37.037 --> 10:40.040
Congressman, I've looked
at the data, and you should--

10:40.040 --> 10:42.109
this meeting is over,
senator.

10:42.109 --> 10:45.112
Oh, and, uh, why don't you
tell your father for me,

10:45.112 --> 10:50.017
next time you see him--
I hope he rots in hell.

10:50.017 --> 10:53.086
(Clark) Okay,
we’ve got a problem.

10:53.086 --> 10:55.122
I'm gonna pull back
on the o'l joystick,

10:55.122 --> 10:58.025
see if we can
get up above it.

10:58.025 --> 10:59.092
Brian?

10:59.092 --> 11:02.062
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!
What?! What?!

11:02.062 --> 11:04.031
He's really praying!
(Engine whines)

11:04.031 --> 11:07.067
What's that noise?
Nick, what's that sound?

11:07.067 --> 11:09.036
Clark?

11:09.036 --> 11:11.038
Can't chat, Mr. George.

11:11.038 --> 11:13.040
Sorry. Little busy here.

11:13.040 --> 11:16.109
But, uh, you should go ahead
and buckle those seat belts.

11:16.109 --> 11:19.012
(Chime dings)

11:19.012 --> 11:21.048
Sweetie... Nick, Nick--

11:21.048 --> 11:24.051
hey, Karen!
I know I said this before,

11:24.051 --> 11:26.119
but if there was ever a time
to say it again, it's now.
What, Karen?

11:26.119 --> 11:29.022
I don't know if you've ever
really believed me,

11:29.022 --> 11:31.091
but I love you, Nick.
I really do.
You gotta be kidding me.

11:31.091 --> 11:33.994
Karen.
Yeah.

11:33.994 --> 11:36.063
I don't know what in life
or just everything that has

11:36.063 --> 11:39.099
kept us and made it impossible
for us to be together,

11:39.099 --> 11:42.102
but I do know in my heart...

11:42.102 --> 11:45.005
You're the one.
You always have been.

11:46.106 --> 11:48.008
Oh, God.

11:48.008 --> 11:52.012
Oh, God!
This is it!

11:52.012 --> 11:54.114
(Air whooshing)

11:54.114 --> 11:56.049
(Whooshing stops)

11:56.049 --> 11:58.118
(Clark) Sorry about that.

11:58.118 --> 12:02.022
Got a little hairy there,
but, uh, were fine.

12:02.022 --> 12:05.092
Why don't you just, uh,
sit back, relax,

12:05.092 --> 12:07.094
enjoy the flight, and, uh,

12:07.094 --> 12:11.098
just--just go back to doing
whatever you were doing?

12:16.036 --> 12:19.006
Here you go.

12:19.006 --> 12:21.041
Okay.

12:23.010 --> 12:25.045
So...

12:25.045 --> 12:27.080
What?

12:27.080 --> 12:29.116
You were saying?

12:38.091 --> 12:41.028
Where the hell are we?

12:41.028 --> 12:43.096
We are just outside
of wilkes-barre.

12:43.096 --> 12:44.131
Pennsylvania?

12:44.131 --> 12:46.099
Yeah.

12:46.099 --> 12:49.102
Hey, get back in that cockpit
and fly us outta here.

12:49.102 --> 12:51.038
No can do, sir.

12:51.038 --> 12:54.074
The F. A. A. Has grounded
all flights into Dulles

12:54.074 --> 12:57.010
due to heavy winds.
Wind? You're afraid
of a little wind?!

12:57.010 --> 12:59.046
Just man up you big...
Sissy!

12:59.046 --> 13:01.048
Hey, it's not
his fault, Brian.

13:01.048 --> 13:04.017
Hey, what are you in such
a rush for anyway?

13:04.017 --> 13:06.053
Because I made a commitment.

13:06.053 --> 13:10.057
People are counting on me.
I care.

13:10.057 --> 13:12.059
Yeah, I have
an appointment, too,

13:12.059 --> 13:15.028
but you don't see me
throwing a hissy fit.
Well, I'd be calm, too,

13:15.028 --> 13:18.999
if I had a river of vodka
running through me.
Hey. Hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey.

13:18.999 --> 13:22.102
You know what?
Let's just drive.

13:25.105 --> 13:27.107
I don't see
why you get to drive.

13:27.107 --> 13:30.010
Because you drive
like grandma Darling.

13:30.010 --> 13:32.012
Yeah,
and you drive like Bo Duke.

13:32.012 --> 13:35.048
Hey, come on, Brian.
You're going 90. Slow down.
Hey, I've got places to go.

13:35.048 --> 13:38.051
So do we.
Yeah, and we'd like
to get there alive.

13:38.051 --> 13:40.120
Damn it.
What?

13:40.120 --> 13:43.090
I gotta pee.
(Tires squeal)

13:45.092 --> 13:48.028
Don't worry.
I'm not gonna bring it up...

13:48.028 --> 13:50.030
The thing you said
on the plane...

13:50.030 --> 13:52.032
Good.
About me being the one.

13:52.032 --> 13:55.035
I'm glad you're not
gonna bring it up.
I don't need to.

13:55.035 --> 13:57.104
I've heard enough declarations
of love in my life

13:57.104 --> 14:00.040
