Yeah, if we'd grown up
in Bombay.

27:41.656 --> 27:44.592
Mm. (Laughs)

27:44.592 --> 27:47.595
(TV playing indistinctly)

28:04.646 --> 28:06.714
(Knock on door)

28:12.654 --> 28:14.622
Hey.

28:14.622 --> 28:15.690
Hi.

28:15.690 --> 28:18.693
Thanks for meeting me
halfway.

28:18.693 --> 28:21.629
No problem.

28:23.665 --> 28:26.668
Nice place.

28:26.668 --> 28:29.704
Not exactly my idea
of a love nest.

28:29.704 --> 28:34.609
Well, you know,
man plans, God laughs.

28:34.609 --> 28:37.679
It's a long story.

28:39.647 --> 28:41.649
You look good.

28:43.618 --> 28:45.620
So do you.

28:50.592 --> 28:52.627
(Sighs)

28:54.662 --> 28:56.698
You gonna
keep the collar on?

28:56.698 --> 28:58.666
You want me to?

28:58.666 --> 29:00.635
No. I don't know.

29:00.635 --> 29:03.605
I've never done this before.

29:03.605 --> 29:05.607
Well, neither have I.

29:05.607 --> 29:07.609
I mean, technically.

29:07.609 --> 29:10.645
I've only cheated on you...

29:10.645 --> 29:12.647
Not with you.

29:15.617 --> 29:18.653
You're such a bastard.

29:18.653 --> 29:20.655
(Chuckles)

29:33.601 --> 29:34.702
(Woman) ♪ one more stop ♪

29:34.702 --> 29:37.639
Why isn't Brian coming along?

29:37.639 --> 29:38.706
I don't know.

29:38.706 --> 29:40.708
I am not
my half brother's keeper.

29:40.708 --> 29:42.710
(Laughs)

29:42.710 --> 29:45.613
(Cell phone rings)

29:45.613 --> 29:46.648
(Ring)

29:46.648 --> 29:47.682
Hello.

29:47.682 --> 29:50.652
Yes.

29:50.652 --> 29:53.688
Oh, okay. Yeah.

29:53.688 --> 29:56.691
Thank you.
All right. Bye.
Who was that?

29:56.691 --> 29:58.693
Um, my doctor in New York.

29:58.693 --> 30:00.695
He was the one who did
the physical.

30:00.695 --> 30:02.697
Just calling to confirm

30:02.697 --> 30:05.633
that all of my lady parts
are good to go.

30:05.633 --> 30:07.602
Ah.

30:09.704 --> 30:11.639
(Charles) Senator.

30:11.639 --> 30:12.707
Another potcheen, please,

30:12.707 --> 30:14.709
and one for
my esteemed colleague

30:14.709 --> 30:16.678
from across the aisle.

30:16.678 --> 30:18.680
To what do I owe
the pleasure, senator?

30:18.680 --> 30:20.715
Your father running low
on whipping boys?

30:20.715 --> 30:22.717
The opposite.

30:22.717 --> 30:24.719
I've come to apologize

30:24.719 --> 30:27.689
for my complete ignorance
earlier.

30:27.689 --> 30:29.691
I think I understand now

30:29.691 --> 30:31.693
why you were
so frustrated with me.

30:31.693 --> 30:35.597
You do?

30:35.597 --> 30:37.632
Really?

30:37.632 --> 30:38.700
Of course.

30:38.700 --> 30:40.635
I've been subjected to

30:40.635 --> 30:43.638
a lifetime of bullying
from my father.

30:43.638 --> 30:46.708
It stands to reason
I haven't been the only one.

30:46.708 --> 30:49.711
Listen, I know my father

30:49.711 --> 30:52.614
will never give you
the apology you deserve,

30:52.614 --> 30:55.617
but, uh, I hope
you will accept mine.

30:55.617 --> 30:57.685
Whatever he did
to pressure you...

30:57.685 --> 30:59.654
I'm sorry.

30:59.654 --> 31:02.690
(Instrumental piano music
playing)

31:07.695 --> 31:10.598
Apology accepted.

31:10.598 --> 31:12.634
Great.

31:12.634 --> 31:13.701
Terrific.

31:13.701 --> 31:16.638
(Laughs)

31:16.638 --> 31:20.642
Well, I hope this means
we can... move forward.

31:20.642 --> 31:23.645
Oh, I hope so, too.

31:32.654 --> 31:34.589
Excuse me?

31:34.589 --> 31:35.623
What?

31:35.623 --> 31:37.692
(Scoffs)
What the hell was that?

31:40.628 --> 31:43.631
I thought you understood
what your father had on me.

31:48.670 --> 31:51.706
You... have a wife
and children.

31:51.706 --> 31:54.609
And you have a thing
for transsexuals.

31:54.609 --> 31:58.680
Yeah, with... female parts.

31:58.680 --> 32:01.616
I'm, uh...

32:01.616 --> 32:02.684
I'm not gay.

32:06.621 --> 32:09.657
Oh, um...

32:09.657 --> 32:11.659
I'm sorry...

32:11.659 --> 32:14.596
For the confusion,
senator.

32:14.596 --> 32:16.598
And I'm sorry...

32:16.598 --> 32:17.665
(Gulps) Ahh...

32:17.665 --> 32:20.668
But you won't
be getting my vote.

32:25.673 --> 32:29.611
That went well.

32:30.712 --> 32:33.648
Don't wander off.

32:35.617 --> 32:37.719
(Car door closes)

32:42.690 --> 32:44.692
Dad!

32:44.692 --> 32:48.663
(Grunts) How are you?
Are you having fun?

32:48.663 --> 32:51.699
Yeah. Now that you're here,
though, it's even better.

32:51.699 --> 32:53.701
Well, thank you.

32:53.701 --> 32:56.604
(Grunts)
Oh. Your mom's here.

32:56.604 --> 32:58.606
Why are you doing this?

32:58.606 --> 33:01.609
Well, like I said,
this is my weekend with Kiki,

33:01.609 --> 33:04.612
so I thought I'd come
and pick her up.
You drove all the way here
for me?

33:04.612 --> 33:06.648
Of course I did.

33:06.648 --> 33:09.651
You can't just show up here
unannounced, Nick.

33:09.651 --> 33:11.719
We--we talked about this.
No, we didn't talk
about anything.

33:11.719 --> 33:13.721
That's why
I had to drive down here.

33:13.721 --> 33:15.723
Ten minutes to dinnertime,
baby doll.

33:15.723 --> 33:18.626
Oh. Hi.

33:19.694 --> 33:21.696
Baby doll?

33:21.696 --> 33:23.665
Edward, this is Nick.

33:23.665 --> 33:27.669
Nick.
I've heard a lot about you.

33:27.669 --> 33:30.605
Hi.

33:32.707 --> 33:34.642
Hey, hey, Kiki,

33:34.642 --> 33:37.645
would you mind staying here
for a second with Edward?

33:37.645 --> 33:39.714
I just want to talk
to your mom.

33:39.714 --> 33:41.716
(Lisa)
Okay. Be right back.

33:41.716 --> 33:43.718
What the hell
is going on here?

33:43.718 --> 33:45.653
He's my client.

33:45.653 --> 33:47.655
Well, unless you're
a prostitute,

33:47.655 --> 33:49.657
he's obviously much more
than just a client.
Funny.

33:49.657 --> 33:52.594
Edward invited me here
to update his art collection.

33:52.594 --> 33:54.662
We're getting along.
Oh, well, obviously.
Baby doll?

33:54.662 --> 33:56.698
You and I have been separated
for two months, Nick.

33:56.698 --> 33:59.701
I am allowed to date.
Lisa, you didn't inform me
you were taking our daughter,

33:59.701 --> 34:02.637
and you took her
across state lines.
Oh, don't talk to me
like we're in court.

34:02.637 --> 34:05.673
I'm not on the stand, Nick,
and you are not the judge.

34:05.673 --> 34:08.710
What, you want to tell me
that you've been so pure?
I never said I was pure.

34:08.710 --> 34:11.713
(Chuckles) Talk about getting
in bed with your clients.

34:11.713 --> 34:14.649
Hey, whatever I am,
I'm still Kiki's father.

34:14.649 --> 34:16.650
And for our daughter's sake...

34:16.650 --> 34:18.652
I'm not gonna cause a scene.

34:18.652 --> 34:20.588
I'm gonna get outta here.

34:20.588 --> 34:22.657
But you know and I know
that after this little stunt

34:22.657 --> 34:24.626
you'll never get
full custody now.

34:24.626 --> 34:26.628
50-50 is the best
you can hope for,

34:26.628 --> 34:28.630
which is what I've been
offering all along.

34:28.630 --> 34:31.632
Now you make sure
that Kiki's back by Monday.

34:33.668 --> 34:35.703
Hey, Kiki.

34:37.672 --> 34:40.708
Man, I had no idea you were
having such a good time,

34:40.708 --> 34:42.710
and I gotta get back
to the city.

34:42.710 --> 34:44.646
So is it okay

34:44.646 --> 34:47.649
if we see each other
when you get back into town?
Okay.

34:47.649 --> 34:49.650
All right, hug. (Groans)

34:49.650 --> 34:51.652
Bye.

34:52.687 --> 34:53.721
Dad.

34:53.721 --> 34:55.657
Yeah.

34:55.657 --> 34:56.690
I love you.

34:58.693 --> 35:00.695
I love you, too.

35:05.700 --> 35:08.603
You ready for dinner?

35:08.603 --> 35:10.605
Come on.

35:20.682 --> 35:22.650
Simon.

35:22.650 --> 35:24.719
What did you say
to Jeremy?

35:24.719 --> 35:27.722
About what?
Me.

35:27.722 --> 35:32.594
Triton, go start the car.

35:32.594 --> 35:33.695
Tell me what happened.

35:33.695 --> 35:35.697
He came screaming at me

35:35.697 --> 35:38.633
saying that
you told him everything

35:38.633 --> 35:40.635
about how I was plotting
against the family,

35:40.635 --> 35:42.637
trying to tear them apart.

35:42.637 --> 35:45.640
I told him he didn't understand,
and then he hit me.

35:45.640 --> 35:49.644
(Scoffs) I assure you, I didn't
tell him to do that. Not at all.

35:49.644 --> 35:51.679
Simon. Simon--
look, I am under
a lot of pressure right now.

35:51.679 --> 35:54.616
Pressure
you know nothing about.

35:54.616 --> 35:56.651
If you want to make it easy
for yourself,

35:56.651 --> 35:58.686
stay away from Jeremy Darling.

35:58.686 --> 36:02.657
(Screaming)

36:02.657 --> 36:06.628
(Car alarm blaring)

36:06.628 --> 36:07.695
(Woman screams)

36:07.695 --> 36:11.699
(Alarm continues)

36:11.699 --> 36:13.701
That was meant for you.

36:25.580 --> 36:27.615
Looks like
smooth sailing tonight, folks.

36:27.615 --> 36:30.652
So, uh, we should be home
in no time.

36:30.652 --> 36:32.620
(Nick) You've been quiet.

36:33.688 --> 36:36.691
Mei ling
lightened your mood?

36:36.691 --> 36:39.694
She... changed it.

36:39.694 --> 36:43.665
Was it everything
you expected it to be?

36:43.665 --> 36:47.635
You want to hear
all the dirty details?

36:47.635 --> 36:49.704
(Lowered voice)
She came to the motel.

36:49.704 --> 36:51.673
I invited her in.

36:51.673 --> 36:54.676
She took off her coat.

36:54.676 --> 36:58.613
We sat on the bed
for 20 minutes,

36:58.613 --> 37:02.684
17 of which...
I talked about Andrea.

37:02.684 --> 37:04.719
And that was it.

37:08.623 --> 37:12.594
So you didn't
go through with it?

37:13.695 --> 37:17.632
No, I didn't.
I couldn't.

37:17.632 --> 37:18.700
Huh.

37:18.700 --> 37:22.704
Those last three minutes...
I tried.

37:22.704 --> 37:24.639
(Laughs)

37:24.639 --> 37:26.708
The monster
wouldn't come to life.

37:26.708 --> 37:28.643
Hmm.

37:28.643 --> 37:31.646
Well, maybe it's
for the best, Brian.

37:31.646 --> 37:33.648
You're actually
one step closer

37:33.648 --> 37:35.717
to committing to something,

37:35.717 --> 37:37.652
to someone
you really love.

37:37.652 --> 37:39.654
Yeah? What about you?

37:39.654 --> 37:41.689
Wh-wh-what do you mean,
me and...

37:41.689 --> 37:43.691
Me and Karen?

37:43.691 --> 37:45.627
Yeah.

37:45.627 --> 37:47.629
(Mutters)

37:47.629 --> 37:50.698
The two of you having
a kid would be weird, sure,

37:50.698 --> 37:52.667
but it wouldn't be

37:52.667 --> 37:55.703
the worst thing
that ever happened.

38:05.613 --> 38:08.650
Oh, it's so good to be home.

38:08.650 --> 38:13.621
That was exhausting.

38:13.621 --> 38:15.623
Oh, hey.

38:15.623 --> 38:18.693
Thanks for the lift. I owe you
4 bucks for the tolls.

38:18.693 --> 38:20.628
See ya.

38:20.628 --> 38:22.597
See ya.

38:22.597 --> 38:24.632
Hey, Karen.
Here.

38:24.632 --> 38:28.636
I know what it's like to want
to have a child. I do.

38:28.636 --> 38:30.705
And I don't know
if I ever told you this,

38:30.705 --> 38:33.641
but Lisa and I had to try
for six months

38:33.641 --> 38:35.710
before we got pregnant
with Kiki.

38:35.710 --> 38:37.679
And I remember
what it was like...

38:37.679 --> 38:40.648
Laying in bed thinking about
this little person

38:40.648 --> 38:42.717
I wanted so badly to meet.

38:42.717 --> 38:45.620
She just wouldn't show up,

38:45.620 --> 38:48.590
and it drove me crazy.

38:48.590 --> 38:49.657
Oh...

38:51.626 --> 38:52.694
You know how I feel.

38:52.694 --> 38:55.663
That's a--that's
a real consolation, Nick.

38:55.663 --> 38:57.599
Thanks.

38:57.599 --> 38:59.601
Hey, no. Karen, Karen,
I guess what I'm--

38:59.601 --> 39:02.670
what I'm trying
to tell you is...

39:02.670 --> 39:04.606
I love you.

39:06.608 --> 39:08.676
I do.

39:08.676 --> 39:12.614
And I am open
to being your baby daddy.

39:12.614 --> 39:14.616
(Chuckles)

39:14.616 --> 39:16.684
What--you're--you're open--
you're open to--

39:16.684 --> 39:18.720
you're open to it?
Yeah.

39:18.720 --> 39:21.656
I can't do it yet,
and I'm--and I'm sorry.

39:21.656 --> 39:23.691
But I-I can't.
I can't do it yet.

39:23.691 --> 39:26.594
Ok-okay.

39:26.594 --> 39:28.630
But if we were
to take things slow,

39:28.630 --> 39:30.665
like... with us--

39:30.665 --> 39:32.667
like--like going out?
Yeah.

39:32.667 --> 39:34.702
Yeah.
Yeah, going out.

39:34.702 --> 39:40.642
Maybe it wouldn't be
such a long way away.

39:40.642 --> 39:43.711
We might get there sooner
than either one of us thinks.

39:47.649 --> 39:49.584
What's wrong?

39:49.584 --> 39:50.585
Nothing.

39:50.585 --> 39:52.587
Karen, I--

39:52.587 --> 39:53.655
that was just--
that was...

39:53.655 --> 39:55.690
(Chuckles)
That was really...

39:55.690 --> 39:57.692
(Voice breaks)
That was really sweet,

39:57.692 --> 40:00.662
what you just said.

40:07.669 --> 40:09.671
Get some sleep.

40:16.611 --> 40:17.645
(Letitia) Dear?

40:17.645 --> 40:20.648
I thought that was you.

40:22.684 --> 40:25.687
Oh... what's wrong?

40:25.687 --> 40:29.624
I'm pregnant.

40:29.624 --> 40:30.658
Already?

40:30.658 --> 40:32.660
My, those sperm banks
are very efficient.

40:32.660 --> 40:35.663
No, no, no, no. No, no,
mom, mom, it isn't...

40:35.663 --> 40:38.633
It doesn't have anything
to do with sperm banks.

40:38.633 --> 40:40.702
It's--the doctor
that gave me the physical,

40:40.702 --> 40:43.605
he called this morning.
I'm pregnant.

40:43.605 --> 40:44.672
With Simon's baby?

40:44.672 --> 40:46.608
With Simon's baby.

40:46.608 --> 40:48.610
Oh, no.

40:48.610 --> 40:49.677
I know.

40:49.677 --> 40:51.613
Oh. Oh.

40:51.613 --> 40:54.649
Oh, my God.

40:54.649 --> 40:57.619
Mm.

40:57.619 --> 40:59.621
Oh, baby.

41:02.724 --> 41:07.339
Jeremy, I'm sorry I had to
call you over so late.

41:09.275 --> 41:12.278
Thanks for coming.

41:12.278 --> 41:14.346
Thanks for having me...

41:14.346 --> 41:16.348
I think.

41:18.317 --> 41:21.287
I'm sure you heard
about the maybach...

41:23.289 --> 41:25.324
And triton.

41:25.324 --> 41:28.360
Well, I've--
I've got a vague memory.

41:28.360 --> 41:30.296
Vague? (Laughs)

41:30.296 --> 41:33.299
You got a lot more
than a vague memory.

41:33.299 --> 41:35.367
Let's cut to the chase,
Jeremy.

41:35.367 --> 41:38.270
I know
you don't have amnesia.

41:38.270 --> 41:40.339
(Scoffs) If--if I
remember correctly, I do.

41:40.339 --> 41:43.342
Do not waste my time.
See, I got this gut instinct

41:43.342 --> 41:45.344
that says
you're not the kind of guy

41:45.344 --> 41:47.346
who's gonna punch
a woman in the face.

41:47.346 --> 41:50.282
That sounds a lot more
like Nola’s idea.
(Mutters)

41:50.282 --> 41:51.350
It's okay.
Jeremy, it's okay.

41:51.350 --> 41:54.320
Because, see,
you failed at fooling me

41:54.320 --> 41:56.322
about the status
of your memory,

41:56.322 --> 41:58.324
but you succeeded
in communicating to me

41:58.324 --> 42:01.327
how much you care for her
and her little brother.

42:01.327 --> 42:04.263
Brother? Uh, I didn't know
she had a brother.

42:04.263 --> 42:07.266
Yeah, yeah, you did. Now this
is what we're gonna do.

42:07.266 --> 42:09.301
See, I'm gonna let you be
the big hero.

42:09.301 --> 42:14.273
I'll arrange things so you can
rescue Nola’s brother.

42:14.273 --> 42:17.276
But I'll need something
from you.

42:17.276 --> 42:19.311
What?

42:19.311 --> 42:22.281
I'm gonna need you
to kill someone.

42:26.285 --> 42:27.319
Who?

42:35.327 --> 42:36.257
Me.
